OAuth 2.0 Authentication
Why OAuth?
In microservices architecture, backend services need to communicate securely without exposing user credentials.

Write on Medium
Scenario:

User logs into banking app (provides username/password once)
Homepage makes an “Account Overview” API call
This call internally calls: Balance API, Credit Card API, Profile API
Problem: Passing user credentials to every internal API is insecure.

Solution: OAuth 2.0 — an authorization framework where services use access tokens instead of credentials.

OAuth Architecture
┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐
│   Client    │────▶│ Authorization   │────▶│  Resource    │
│  (App/API)  │     │     Server      │     │   Server     │
└─────────────┘     └─────────────────┘     └──────────────┘
       │                     │                       │
       │  1. Client ID +     │                       │
       │     Client Secret   │                       │
       │   ─────────────────▶│                       │
       │                     │                       │
       │  2. Access Token    │                       │
       │   ◀─────────────────│                       │
       │                     │                       │
       │  3. Token + Request │                       │
       │   ─────────────────────────────────────────▶│
       │                     │                       │
       │  4. Response        │                       │
       │   ◀─────────────────────────────────────────│
