Best Practices & Interview Questions
Best Practices
Always clean up test data — Delete created resources after test
Use DataProvider for multiple data sets — Avoid code duplication
Store credentials securely — Use environment variables, never hardcode
Handle token expiration — Implement refresh token logic for long-running tests
Log requests/responses — Use .log().all() during development
Validate status codes — Always assert expected status (200, 201, etc.)
Common Interview Questions
Q1: How do you handle dynamic payloads in REST Assured?
A: Use string concatenation or a method that accepts parameters and returns the JSON string.

Q2: What is TestNG DataProvider?
A: An annotation that returns a 2D array of data. Test method runs once for each inner array, receiving array elements as parameters.

Q3: How do you upload a file using REST Assured?
A: Use .multiPart(key, new File(path)). REST Assured automatically sets multipart/form-data content type.

Q4: Explain OAuth 2.0 client credentials grant flow.
A: Client sends client_id and client_secret to authorization server, receives access token, then uses token to access protected resources.

Q5: How do you authenticate Jira API?
A: Basic authentication with Base64-encoded email:api_token. Generate API token from Jira account settings.

Q6: Difference between queryParam, formParam, and pathParam?
A:

queryParam → URL query string (?key=value)
formParam → Form data in body (application/x-www-form-urlencoded)
pathParam → Replaces {variable} in URL path
