12. Best Practices Summary
Always parse request body using JSON.parse(pm.request.body.raw) – never assume pm.request.json() exists.

Use data files for large sets of test inputs; do not hardcode test data.

Generate unique identifiers (ISBNs, emails, etc.) with dynamic variables to avoid conflicts.

Implement try-catch in tests that might fail due to expected race conditions (e.g., duplicates).

Control flow with postman.setNextRequest() only when needed; always provide an exit condition to avoid infinite loops.

Use a flag variable to remember state when jumping between requests.

Write reusable functions for repeated logic (ID generation, cleanup, etc.).

Validate JSON schemas to ensure API contract compliance.

Log extensively during script development, then remove or comment out logs for production runs.

Reset state variables (like flags) at the beginning of workflows.

