1. Understanding Mock Servers

What is a Mock Server?

A mock API server imitates a real API server by providing realistic mock responses to requests

Used when production API is not ready or you don't want to run requests against real data yet

Postman allows you to create mock servers that return predefined responses

Why Use Mock Servers in Agile Development?

Real-world scenario:
Development team needs 2 weeks to complete an API

As a tester, you don't need to wait idle

Create a mock server and complete automation scripts in parallel

Key benefits:
Parallel work with developers - no waiting for actual code

Meet sprint deadlines (e.g., 10-day sprints)

Test automation can be completed before real API is ready

Simply flip the URL from mock to real server when code is deployed

How Mock Servers Work

text
Tester Request → Mock Server (Postman) → Predefined Mock Response
                    ↓
            (When real API ready)
                    ↓
Tester Request → Real API Server → Actual Response

2. JSON Schema Fundamentals

What is JSON Schema?

A blueprint/contract defining how a JSON response should look

Specifies required fields, data types, and structure

Allows validation of API responses against expected format

JSON Schema Example Structure

json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema#",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "data": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": [{
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "course": { "type": "string" },
