Part 9: Common Interview Questions (With Clear Answers)

Basic questions
What is a web service? - Communication between two applications over the web, independent of language and platform.

Difference between SOAP and REST? - SOAP is a strict protocol using XML; REST is an architectural style usually using JSON and HTTP methods.

What is WSDL? - Web Services Description Language - an XML document that describes a SOAP service (operations, parameters, data types, location).

What is SoapUI? - A testing tool for web services and REST APIs (open‑source).

Can SoapUI test REST APIs? - Yes, it supports both SOAP and REST.

Intermediate questions
