8.1 Keep Tests Deterministic
A test should produce the same result every time it runs.

Avoid dependencies on changing data, current time, or external systems that vary unpredictably.

8.2 Design Tests for Change
Web services evolve. Focus tests on business‑critical functionality.

Use properties and configuration files so that URLs, ports, and environment values can be swapped easily.

8.3 Manage Test Data Intentionally
Generate test data explicitly for each run rather than relying on pre‑existing records.

Use unique identifiers (e.g., timestamp in employee name) to avoid conflicts.

Clean up test data after the test (delete the employee).

8.4 Validate Meaningfully
Do not stop at HTTP status codes. Always verify:
Response structure (valid XML/JSON).

Key data values (e.g., age, department).

Error messages for negative scenarios.

Business rule enforcement.

8.5 Test Both Positive and Negative Cases
Positive: Add valid employee → expect true.

