9. Advanced Scripting - Context Variables and Message Exchange
9.1 Access Limitations in Different Script Windows
Different script windows have different available objects:
Setup Script (test case level) - has context, testRunner, log.

TearDown Script - same as Setup.

Script Assertion - has messageExchange, log, and limited context.

Groovy Script TestStep - full access to context, testRunner, log, messageExchange.

9.2 Passing Values Between Different Script Contexts
Setting a property in a Groovy Script TestStep:
context.setProperty('tempId', '12345')

Reading it in a subsequent Script Assertion:
def tempId = context.getProperty('tempId')

Note: If you set a property in a Script Assertion, it may not persist to other steps. Best practice: Use testRunner.testCase.setPropertyValue() for cross‑step sharing.

9.3 When to Use Property Transfer vs Script (No Table - Bulleted List)
Use Property Transfer (built‑in) when:
You need simple XPath extraction.

Non‑technical team members will maintain the tests.

You want zero coding overhead.

Use Scripting (Groovy) when:
Complex logic is required (loops, conditions, transformations).

You need full control and error handling.

You want reusable functions across projects.

Recommendation: Start with Property Transfer; switch to Groovy when you need conditions, calculations, or custom error handling.

